.TH popwrd 8
.SH NAME
\*Lpopwrd\*O \- Sets password for a POP subscriber
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*L/usr/local/lib/mh/popwrd\*O \*VPOP-subscriber\*O
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "popwrd command"
The \*Lpopwrd\*O program lets the superuser or the master Post Office
Protocol (POP) user or a "leader" of a POP subscriber change the password
field for the POP subscriber in the POP database. This program is very
similar to the \*Lpasswd\*O(1) program.
.PP
Since only the superuser and the master POP user can change any
other fields of the POP database (using an ordinary editor), it is
possible for the system administrator to delegate responsibility to
others to manage groups of POP subscribers.
.SH FILES
.VL 11m
.LI "\*L/usr/spool/pop/POP\*O"
Specifies the POP database.
